== Verb ==

'''Open a can of Whoop Ass'''

US pop-culture [[slang]] (Late 1980’s/ early 1990’s) commonly used as a good humoured threat meaning that the speaker may soon initiate the breaking loose of all hell. Also spelt Whup ass.
<br><br>
The origin of this figurative anarchy-related phrase is presently unknown, although its usage is closely associated with the [[A Team]] TV program character BA Barracus ([[Mr. T]]). It has appeared in several movies including [[Bruce Almighty]], [[The Waterboy]].

''Common Usage:'' "I'm gonna open up a can of whoop-ass on ya",